Initially, a total of 9844 articles were identified through a comprehensive search of the Scopus and WOS databases, comprising 1249 and 8572 articles, respectively. After eliminating 521 duplicate articles, 9323 articles remained for screening. Full text screening was conducted for 308 studies to determine their eligibility based on the predefined inclusion criteria outlined in Table 2
                        . The rigorous screening process culminated in the selection of 89 studies from which qualitative data was extracted (see Fig. 1
                        ).

In terms of spatial scope , out of 89 studies, 47 (53Â %) articles evaluated biofuels at the national scale, while 33 (37Â %) had a regional coverage, and nine (10Â %) carried multi-country evaluation of biofuels (see Fig. 2
                     ). With respect to evaluated biofuel types, 44 studies (49Â %) were solely focused on biodiesel, while 19 (21Â %) exclusively examined bioethanol (Fig. 3
                     ). 25 (28Â %) studies covered both ethanol and biodiesel and only one study evaluated the effects of other country biofuel policy on India.
